      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You absolutely need to avoid alcohol while taking metronidazole. Mixing it with wine can cause a severe reaction called disulfiram-like reaction, which involves nausea, vomiting, and a pounding headache. To be safe, you should wait until you have finished the entire course of your medication before you even think about having a glass of wine. Stick to clear liquids until the prescription is completely done.",
